page.title: 10GREENTHWAITE GRANGE
page.content: This square kilometre lies between the class 2 road B1363 to the east and a local traffic road Bull Lane which runs parallel to it. There are two farms in the area - Greenthwaite Grange and Broad Acres. Greenthwaite Grange stands at the edge of a very small wooded area. There is a small man-made pond at Greenthwaite Grange. All the fields are bordered by hawthorn hedges with some well-established deciduous trees. A line of electric pylons crosses the north-east corner of the area. A small stream in a deep ditch runs across the top of the area from east to west.
